net.imglib2.cache.img

Class LoadedCellCacheLoader<T extends NativeType<T>,A extends ArrayDataAccess<A>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.imglib2.cache.img.LoadedCellCacheLoader<T,A>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - pixel type
    A - access type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CacheLoader<Long,Cell<A>>

    public class LoadedCellCacheLoader<T extends NativeType<T>,A extends ArrayDataAccess<A>>
extends Object
implements CacheLoader<Long,Cell<A>>
    A CacheLoader that produces cells of ArrayDataAccess type A and uses a CellLoader to populate them with data.

    Usually, LoadedCellCacheLoader should be created through static helper methods get(CellGrid, CellLoader, NativeType, Set) or get(CellGrid, CellLoader, NativeType, PrimitiveType, Set) to get the desired primitive type and dirty/volatile variant.

    Author:
    Tobias Pietzsch
